    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Designing clothing, accessories, and ensembles for personal wear. For the design of clothing, accessories, and ensembles intended to create an appearance characteristic of a particular period, person, place, or thing, especially (but not exclusively) for theatrical performances, use "costume design."  For the concept of a prevailing, usually short lived custom, usage, or style in clothing, cars, restaurants, and other personal possessions and services, use "fashion."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Diseño de vestuario, accesorios y conjuntos para uso personal. Para el diseño de vestuario, accesorios y conjuntos pretendiendo crear una apariencia característica de un periodo, persona, lugar o cosa particular, especialmente (pero no exclusivamente) para representaciones teatrales, use "diseño de vestuario".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Het vormgeven van kleding, accessoires en ensembles voor individuen. Gebruik 'kostuumvormgeving' voor het vormgeven van kleding, accessoires en ensembles die zijn bedoeld om een uiterlijk te creëren dat karakteristiek is voor een bepaalde periode, persoon, plaats of ding, vooral (maar niet uitsluitend) voor theatervoorstellingen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>設計衣服、配件或整體服飾以供人穿著。若指稱衣服、配件與整體服飾的設計，目的為針對特定期間或人、事、場合創造獨特的外型效果，尤其用於（但不全是）戲劇演出的場合，則稱之為「服裝設計」。若指稱流行的概念，且通常為服飾、汽車、餐飲及其他個人持有物與服務上為時短暫的風尚、用途或款式，則稱之為「流行」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Desenhar roupas, acessórios e conjuntos para uso pessoal. Para o design de roupas, acessórios e conjuntos destinados a criar uma aparência característica de um determinado período, pessoa, lugar ou coisa, especialmente (mas não exclusivamente) para apresentações teatrais, use "figurino". Para o conceito de um costume, uso ou estilo prevalecente, geralmente de curta duração, em roupas, carros, restaurantes e outros bens pessoais e serviços, use "moda </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
